dataset.description:
The 2007 OSIP digital orthophotography was collected during the months of March and April (leaf-off conditions).

The MrSID Images covering each county at 1-foot pixel resolution will be created at a 30:1 compression ratio.  At a 30:1 compression ratio, the resulting MrSID file size will average around 2GBs in size (dependent upon county size).

MrSID Images will also be created for each buy-up county.  These MrSIDs, will be compressed at a 20:1 ratio.  In some cases, buy-up counties have requested a higher compression ratio.
dataset.title: Athens 1ft 2007

dataset.description: The 2014 Athens County Digital Orthoimagery Project - In the Spring of 2014, Athens County obtained new orthoimagery covering the land area of 51.71 square miles. Imagery was collected with Leica ADS80 digital cameras and rectified using LiDAR data. In addition to 4-band, 8-bit orthophotos with a 3-inch ground sample distance GSD product produced include countywide Multi resolution Seamless Image Database - MrSID (individual RGB - 30x and 100x; individual CIR - 30x and 100x). Ownership of the data products resides with Athens County and the state of Ohio. Orthoimagery and ancillary data products produced through this contract are public domain.
dataset.title: Athens 6in 2014
